                            <comment id="127832" author="dinatale2" created="Fri, 18 Sep 2015 18:14:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That fixed it. Not a bug. Apologies!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="127831" author="green" created="Fri, 18 Sep 2015 18:05:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ll_file_noflock is only called when mounted without flock option of with -o noflock.&lt;br/&gt;
-o flock or -o localflock would install different handlers for flock functionality.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="127830" author="dinatale2" created="Fri, 18 Sep 2015 18:03:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No we didn&apos;t. We will do that now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="127829" author="dinatale2" created="Fri, 18 Sep 2015 18:03:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The unimplemented function after looking at lctl debug logs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
